wikipedia_page.main: Henry "Harry" Dupuis (born 24 March 1808, Wendlebury, Oxfordshire; died 3 June 1867, Richmond, Surrey) was an English cricketer with amateur status. He was associated with Cambridge University and made his first-class debut in 1828.Dupuis was educated at Eton College and at King's College, Cambridge, where he became a Fellow after graduation. He became an assistant master at Eton College and, having been ordained, became Church of England vicar of Richmond, Surrey from 1852 up to his death.
